title: Solid State Electronic Circuits - Edward W. Maby
description:
Solid-State Electronic Circuits is a competitively priced companion text for undergraduate students who are interested in analog and digital electronic circuits. Volume 1 covers basic electronic concepts, the physical basis of solid-state devices, and diode circuits and applications. For optimum viewing, use a platform that supports Kindle Fire.
 
Volume 2 covers MOSFET and BJT transistors, mid-frequency amplifier circuits, and high- and low-frequency response.
 
Volume 3 covers op-amp design, CMOS digital circuits, and feedback.


Volume 4 covers analog filters, digital conditioning for serial links, noise, distortion, transmission-line effects, analog-to-digital converters, and digital-to-analog converters
